● Found it. 192.168.103.0/24 is completely missing from the outbound ACCEPT rules. Every other subnet has one:

  192.168.100.0/24 → ACCEPT via eth0 ✅
  192.168.101.x   → ACCEPT via eth0 ✅
  192.168.102.2   → ACCEPT via eth0 ✅
  192.168.104.0/24 → ACCEPT via eth0 ✅
  192.168.103.x   → ❌ MISSING

  Add the rule:

  sudo iptables -I FORWARD -s 192.168.103.0/24 -o eth0 -m state --state NEW -j ACCEPT

  Then make it persistent:

  sudo iptables-save > /etc/iptables/rules.v4

  Once that's done, test from the MSG server that the subnet can reach the internet, then reinstall the VM.



